      "writtenOn": "2019-10-18T06:26:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "from the client perspective, this error message and code are inconsistent with other cases where invocation was interrupted. Normally the client receives `... is not active` but here it receives `has exceeded deadline`. \n\ni think we should return same message as if the invocation is not active. The fact that we have just maked the invocation as interrupted in the database is an impl detail. Then from the client perspective, the invocation looks interrupted before they made the call, and next time they make the call, the receive the same error message, which would be consistent.",
      "revId": "45fd76d41f73f14895463c8b0c4b30fb12f4dd11",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
